title: Around the World in Eighty Days
creator: Jules Verne
description: LibriVox recording of Around the World in Eighty Days by Jules Verne. Enigmatic Phileas Fogg accepts a wager about whether it's possible to circumnavigate the globe in 80 days or under. The book charts his adventures on the way. (Summary by Alex Foster) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (178MB)
